24/02/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Former Prime Minister Adrian Nastase was elected on Friday (February 22nd) as the leader of the National Council of the Socialist Democratic Party (PSD). Nastase, who headed the government between 2000 and 2004, won the support of 418 of the 648 members of the council; 202 voted for his rival, Dan Mircea Popescu. Nastase was elected to the post despite the fact that he is under investigation on suspicions of bribery, blackmail and influence peddling. (Makfax, Rompres - 22/02/08)
